{
  "stem": "11801.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "We'd come to blows, to physical blows, and had to be-- you know, broken-- had to be taken apart.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "But, otherwise, we were taken care of.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "We were very hungry during the war.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "There was very little food.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "But everybody else was hungry, too, so it certainly bothered me, but I never felt discriminated against.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "What we lacked, and I didn't know then, and I figured it out much later, was a close relationship.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "You know, there was nobody to touch you or hug you or say good night or wish you a happy birthday.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "Although we used to celebrate each other's birthdays, you know, between the small group.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "But there was no-- most of the children actually had relatives who used to visit them.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "We did not.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "The Jewish children did not.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there was one other Jewish child in my unit, and he and I were the only ones who never had any visitors.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we did feel kind of left out and a little bit envious of the other kids who-- you know, whoever visited them might bring them some candy or might bring them a-- a toy or something.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The visitors were allowed once a week.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And once a month, the children were allowed to go out, to, you know, to leave the orphanage accompanied by an adult relative who would pick them up.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, of course, on those once a month, then we would be left all alone in-- in this-- in our unit.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We literally were the only ones who didn't have anyone to take us out.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In my unit, there were 60, and we were divided into three different sections.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So there were 20 in my section, but there were really 60 of us.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
